Prerequisites
-------------
On Ubuntu 11.10,
$ sudo apt-get install -y make cmake g++ libboost-dev libboost-program-options-dev libboost-filesystem-dev libboost-system-dev libzeroc-ice34-dev 


Build
-----
$ mkdir .build
$ cd .build
$ cmake ..
$ make -j8


Running flecs-server manually
-----------------------------
Add . (current directory) to LD_LIBRARY_PATH when running flecs-server for
loading container plugins, since the server executable and container plugins
are at the same directory.


Automation with helper scripts
------------------------------
Go to the script directory. Machine names and login account need to be modified
depending on your environment.
$ cd misc/flecs10-20-50

Updates source code on all nodes using git and rebuild.
$ ./update-build.sh

Alternatively, you can copy working copy of the current developmenet machine to
all nodes using scp and rebuild.
$ ./update-build-working-copy.sh

Kill existing flecs services and start flecs-agent-server and flecs-launcher.
$ ./restart-flecs-agent-launcher.sh

Run flecs-agent-client to launch master, servers, and clients on a target
cluster.
